---
title: Meatball Ragù over Parmesan Polenta Elevated Dinners, Impressively Easy
description: Nonna always said there was nothing like homemade meatballs, but we have to say it: these come very close. Thanks to a few clever tricks from our chefs, you’ll enjoy tender pan-seared cooked meatballs simmered in a savory tomato ragú with fresh spinach, all spooned over creamy Parmesan-swirled polenta—in just 15 minutes. And we can attest that it tastes like you spent all day making it.
